name: Booba Sword | Concept LoRA
description:
Booba Sword | Concept LoRA


BOOOOBAA SWORD. This concept is known from the almighty Shogun. Here is one example. Click here :)

Weight can go from 0.5 up to 1.0. I recommend 0.75. Weight can go from 0.7 up to 1.0. I recommend 1. ControlNet will streamline full body shots much easier, or more complex poses. Works with almost every Style, Character and Photorealistic Models (kinda).

The Main triggerword is Booba Sword. I recommend using more weight on this like (Booba Sword:1.2). You can go higher, like (Booba Sword:1.7) and it will give most of the time ruined Style or will mimic the almighty Shogun. Adding electricity works pretty good.

WARNING: This LoRA does have some problems and hits most of the time 4 out of 10 times. Hands are a big problem and Style is changing a little bit. Hand does not connect with the sword and sword does not appear in the right place sometimes. Will be updated soon.

Trigger Word:

Booba Sword or (Booba Sword:1.2)

Helping Prompt:
cleavage, sword, holding sword

Optional Prompt:

electricity

How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Download LoRA

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA and use the triggerword

  • Make sure to change the weight if needed (by default it's :1)

  • Have Fun!
